{
  "text": "where φ is a free boson (See for example Ref. [CITATION_1] ). To evaluate the correlator of many G fields, we multiply out the terms in all combinations. The only terms that can be nonzero, must have overall charge neutrality [1] so that the number of terms e i √ 3φ must be the same as the number of terms of e −i √ 3φ . Thus all terms are of the form i,j∈A;i<j",
  "correct_citation": {
